FBIS4-47884 "drafr087_c_94037" FBIS-AFR-94-087 Daily Report 5 May 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA TEC Contemplating Future of Peacekeeping Force TEC Contemplating Future of Peacekeeping Force MB0505082094 Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network in Afrikaans 0630 GMT 5 May 94 MB0505082094 Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network Afrikaans BFN [Text] The Transitional Executive Council's subcouncil on defense will today decide on the future of the National Peacekeeping Force [NPKF]. A NPKF spokesman, Colonel Coenie van Rensburg, said a new intake by the peace force will also not be trained at De Brug. He said the various forces comprising the peace force no longer have soldiers available. Col. van Rensburg said members of the peace force, after several incidents since their deployment on the East Rand, have not been limited to their bases but are instead performing supporting roles in conjunction with the Defense Force.
